        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Get URL with .html ending with JSoup",
        "body": "<p>I'm trying to connect to a URL with JSoup.<\/p>\n\n<p>When I use the following code<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Jsoup.connect(\"http://www.example.com/\").get();\nJsoup.connect(\"http://www.example.com/example.html\").get();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The first call succeeds and the second raises an exception:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Exception in thread \"main\" java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Malformed URL: http://www.example.com/example.html\n  at org.jsoup.helper.HttpConnection.url(HttpConnection.java:55)\n  at org.jsoup.helper.HttpConnection.connect(HttpConnection.java:27)\n  at org.jsoup.Jsoup.connect(Jsoup.java:73)\n  at webscraper.JsoupTest.main(JsoupTest.java:259)\nCaused by: java.net.MalformedURLException: no protocol: http://www.example.com/example.html\n  at java.net.URL.&lt;init&gt;(URL.java:567)\n  at java.net.URL.&lt;init&gt;(URL.java:464)\n  at java.net.URL.&lt;init&gt;(URL.java:413)\n  at org.jsoup.helper.HttpConnection.url(HttpConnection.java:53)\n  ... 3 more\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I presume it has something to do with \".html\" in the URL.<\/p>\n\n<p>How can I connect to the URL with JSoup?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 14983619,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "jsoup"
        ],
        "score": 2,
