            "last_activity_date": 1361376513,
            "creation_date": 1361375008,
            "body": "<p>It has nothing to do with .html, you have a blank space prefix in your second url.\nRemove the blank space, it will work fine in my side.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can use this <a href=\"http://www.dolcevie.com/js/converter.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">tool<\/a> to convert the asii to hex for lines code seperately, you will notice the second url has a redundant char '1f' on the position of 16.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 14983976,
            "question_id": 14983619,
            "last_edit_date": 1361376513
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/UVQwD.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 1556351,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1447326,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1447326/dstronczak",
                "reputation": 2464,
                "display_name": "dstronczak",
                "accept_rate": 65
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1361449878,
            "creation_date": 1361374581,
            "body": "<p>I guess this is because you should encode the dashes in the URL. Try this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String url = java.net.URLEncoder.encode(\"http://www.example.com/example.html\", \"UTF-8\");\nJsoup.connect(url).get();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Doc: <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/net/URLEncoder.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://docs.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/net/URLEncoder.html<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 14983809,
            "question_id": 14983619,
            "last_edit_date": 1361449878
        }
